    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ASIA PHONE DEAL COMPLETED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Mark Landler</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Court approves acquisition of Hong Kong's Cable and Wireless HKT by Pacific Century Cyberworks; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Hong Kong's flagship telephone company passed into the hands of a two-year-old Internet upstart, as a court approved the acquisition of Cable and Wireless HKT by Pacific Century Cyberworks. The decision, effective Aug. 17, ends a six-month tale that began when Pacific Century undertook a $38.1 billion bid for Cable and Wireless. The company's founder, Richard Li, left, said he would streamline the merged entity's eight divisions into three.</p>
        <p>Mark Landler (NYT)</p>
      </block>
